ical to the Warrior Discipline, except that it would *only* work on undead. That's not unbalancing at all, and, I believe, something that would add to the definition of our class. This is our job, let us do it. Could a warrior still Defensive-vs-undead? Yes. But, we should be more efficient at it than they would be. Perhaps make it the Warrior's Defensive, and add atop that the Undead only Damage Shield we've discussed here for added aggro/damage? A 15 point damage shield that stacks with all other Damage Shields.<br><br>How about making Act of Valor *useful* in this respect: A targetable save, like a Cleric's Death Pact. When the target runs out of hit points, there's a 30% chance that Lay of Hands will go off on them. It, of course, won't stack with the Cleric's Death Pact, but would give the cleric enough time to get their CHeal off. You may or may not agree with me on this part, but, even if we do ave Complete Heal lay of Hands, I don't think it should be a Complete Heal. That, I think, is asking too much. This would be a momentary solution that gives the target a little added time alive, and, we lose the amount of hit points that our LoH healed for. That, in my opinion, is a useful Act of Valor. It puts us in peril and does something valorous. Could this kill us? Definately. AoEing MoBs will sap HPs, and if we're already low when this goes off, we're dead. It can heal for more than the HPs we have, but, that is our instant death. That is an Act of Valor I'd spend my AA points on.<br><br>And, while this is more for shits and giggles, I also like the idea of a questable level 60 spell that's different depending on the deity you worship. I worship Marr, so I'd like to a spell along the lines of Fury of the Lightbringer, a new extended-Yaulp and HoT. What would you like your deity's spell to be?<br><br>=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=<br><br>I'm posting this here for discussion. <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> This is nothing more than wishful thinking,</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> and shouldn't be taken as something VI *should* do for us because we deserve it. Frankly, we don't. Nobody deserves to get any one thing to make them better than another class. And, after talking with several warriors in my guild, I don't think we should get a full-fledged Defensive like theirs at all, but the one I've posted is acceptable and leaves both classes well-defined. Like it or not, that is their class-defining ability and, if you think about it ... we can outtaunt any classes, so if we had Defensive, as many people have already said, Warriors would become obsolete.<br><br>I'm not posting this here for flames. If you post a flame, I won't reply and will probably label you an idiot that can't read. I've posted this here for wishful thinking and discussion, nothing more.<br><br><br>=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=<br>Kryssniall Stormwatcher<br>52nd Paladin of Mithaniel Marr<br>Officer of Runic Lore<br>All-around Suicidal Meatshield<br>Mithaniel Marr Server<br>=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-= <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utalenvorruglia.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Talenvor Ruglia</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 309<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/9/02 11:31:05 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=14774.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Realistic Paladin Defensive and a possible fix for AoV.</span><hr size=1> The undead defensive disc would be great to have.<br><br>As for AoV I'd prefer the skill to be a group wide LoH that would then kill me, or a target group LoH (using /tgb).  Using that along with the Ch LoH skill would be incredibly useful and then I'd consider killing myself to use it =) <p><TABLE><TR><TD><A HREF="http://www.clubfu.com/