 Re: Realistic Paladin Defensive and a possible fix for AoV.</span><hr size=1> For the sake of argument<br><br>What if paladins had the exact same discipline as warriors??/  <br><br>What would happen?  <br><br>IMHO Warriors would be preferd on some raids and paladins on others.  Warriors where aggro was easier to maintain or where hp/ac made the slim differance.  Paladins on mobs who are hardest to maintain aggro.  In most cases thou I believe the task would fal more to who was a better eq player or had a better trust issue with their guild.   <br><br>Am I asking for that?  No<br>What will I always seek? <br>A defense styl ability that allows the paladin to live 85% as long as a similiar warrior would. I think the 15% is enough to defer to warrios on some mobs yet high enough to defer to paladins on others.  To be honest It'd boil right down to a dead heat imho.<br><br>Would I implement such a change on all servers?  Not until I gradualy tested it with established guilds on a very few servers.  Personaly I'd like verant to make a new test srver something like this.<br><br>Verant makes identical copy of all toons from uber guild 001 and then clones them onto a test server.  Then allow that guild to log on the special test server and test it.  Simply posting the guild's name on the eq board would be enough of a drive.  Of corse this special treatment/server would only be used to test such potentialy game balance issues.  <br><br>But hey I'm a dreamer  oh woops forgot their legend servers are test servers woops <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uketherami.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kether Am I</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 523<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/9/02 3:06:19 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=14774.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Realistic Paladin Defensive and a possible fix for AoV.</span><hr size=1> If you give paladin any sort of defensive style discipline of note I would then offer the following changes to 'balance' them:<br><br>Remove CC<br>Remove HWoP<br><br>Otherwise I honestly wouldn't see why warriors wouldn't just make pal/sks to tank because of their otherwise massive benefits in versatility or rng/mnk/rog for damage output.<br><br>Warriors TANK.<br><br>Leave them that.<br><br>There are a myriad of ways a paladin is more useful not tanking. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ucylria.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Cylria</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 111<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/9/02 4:10:20 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=14774.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Realistic Paladin Defensive and a possible fix for AoV.</span><hr size=1> Why leave warriors as the only tanks? Rogues aren't the only damage dealers, yet they still have their perks. Why not do the same with warriors?<br><br>There is only one VI approved strategy, that is tank+heal+damage. If any other strategy would prove effective on a high level encounter, you see a emergency nerf. Likewise is isn't possible to give every class their own 'unique' role in raid encounters. So why not give more than one class the ability to tank or heal effectively, just like damage dealing?<br><br>I suppose we could all make warrior and cleric alts and not take our paladins on raids, instead just bring whatever alt is needed most.<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukassai.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kassai</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 5<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/9/02 4:25:42 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=14774.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Realistic Paladin Defensive and a possible fix for AoV.</span><hr size=1> two words....FIX SANCTIFICATION<br><br>increase the duration to 1min+..and you have a tank who can be used against Exiled..who uses AE FD to lose MT aggro..or Grieg who uses knockback to lose MT aggro.. or Yelinek who also uses knockback... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uceifer.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ceifer</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 167<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/9/02 5:00:04 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=14774.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.pacbell.net/dsantos/babykick.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Realistic Paladin Defensive and a possible fix for AoV.</span><hr size=1> We do have a role on raids though, we support everyone else on the group.  We take care of AE damage while the clerics focus on the main tanks.  We use LH if there is a late CH.  <br><br>Lets say hypothetically VI gave us the exact same defensive discipline as warriors.  Guess what, warriors will still be tanking the mobs.  They still have higher hp, and higher dodge/riposte/parry caps which make them better at tanking. <br><br>Tanking is the warriors job, not ours.  We are very balanced as is now.  Only thing I would like is if they made Sanctification longer in duration; 40 secs would be